Preconditions:
The input array `nums` must not be null.
The input array `nums` must have a length greater than or equal to `k`.
The input integer `k` must be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
The output array `avgs` must not be null.
The output array `avgs` must have a length equal to the length of the input array `nums`.
Each element `avgs[i]` in the output array `avgs` must be the k-radius average for the subarray centered at index `i`.